                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13427363" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 14:53:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First step is to move #createDefaultValidatorProvider out. Similar validating behaviour will be injected as needed by the tests and other components (oak-jcr for one)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427521" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 18:49:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch to add the CommitEditor to the constructor and move the validator stuff to the modules that actually need/use it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;integration tests look good&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427534" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 19:07:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;on second thought, the patch adds to oak-run some validators, but it does not add the dependency to lucene&amp;amp;friends.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m a bit unclear on the scope of oak-run, it should either contain the full validating functionality, so we should add the dependency to pom.xml or not, in which case the patch should not be applied to this module.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427954" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 3 Aug 2012 10:08:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Looks like a good step forward.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FWIW I don&apos;t think all of the tests leveraging RepositoryTestUtils or otherwise creating a ContentRepositoryImpl with the full set of editors and validators really need all those components to be present. Ideally a &lt;b&gt;unit&lt;/b&gt; test should run with as little extra code as possible, only in integration tests should we have all those extra components enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427980" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 3 Aug 2012 10:42:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cool, thanks for the review!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Ideally a unit test should run with as little extra code as possible, only in integration tests should we have all those extra components enabled.&lt;br/&gt;
I fully agree, we can start trimming the test dependencies as soon as this patch is in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427985" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 3 Aug 2012 10:47:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed with revision 1368881.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
